# data.gov.sg API key — REQUIRED for v2 endpoints (MRT train arrival, full
# real-time data) and strongly recommended for higher rate limits on all
# data.gov.sg calls.
#
# Register for a free key at https://data.gov.sg/ → "Register" → "API Key".
# Sign in with your Singpass or email, then create a key. The key is emailed
# to you and looks like a long random string.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the key. `.env` is gitignored.
# Each skill that ships a per-skill copy of singapore_api.py reads the same
# env var; no per-skill config needed.
DATA_GOV_SG_API_KEY=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What works without the key
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The singapore_api client falls back to data.gov.sg v1 when the key is
# unset. v1 still works for:
#   - PSI / PM2.5 / UV / weather forecasts (text)
#   - Real-time rainfall / wind / temperature / humidity
#   - LTA traffic camera images
#   - HDB carpark availability
#   - LTA bus arrival (with caveats — v1 returns less data)
#   - LTA taxi availability
#   - datastore_search (HDB resale, hawker closures, dengue clusters, etc.)
#   - OneMap geocoder (always free, no key needed)
#
# What requires the key
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   - MRT train arrival times (v2-only, not published on v1)
#
# What the key improves
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   - Higher per-minute rate limit (anonymous tier throttles faster)
#   - Flatter response shapes from v2 (less normalisation in our code)
#   - Future endpoints that ship v2-only
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Quick test
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   cd singapore-skills
#   python3 -c "from singapore_api import _api_key; print('key set' if _api_key() else 'NO KEY')"
#   python3 singapore_api.py     # CLI smoke test, reports auth state
